Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.PL (Programming Languages) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of CHC solvers, which are tools used in software engineering and verification, making cs.SE (Software Engineering) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also mentions the use of induction principles, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence and machine learning, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the transformation of CHCs, which is a topic in formal methods and formal languages, making cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) a possible sub-category.
